main event: A report containing various black-and-white photographs of unidentified flying objects (UFOs) was documented on November 21, 1952, in the Caribbean Sea.
interesting points: The report includes numerous photographs showing circular and oval-shaped objects against dark backgrounds., Some images have specific identification codes associated with them., The objects appeared luminous and varied in shape from circular to oval., The report suggests a systematic cataloging of the UFO images., These photographs were part of the project Blue Book investigation by the U.S. Air Force.
sighted object: various unidentified flying objects, including circular and oval shapes
witness description: The report does not mention any witnesses.
